<paragraph id="IFRS03_B39" base="F4231204" principles="no"><paranum>B39</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 3"/><data name="paranum" value="B39"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS03_P0419">After initial recognition, an <xref base="F4230833" href="IFRS03_APPA.dita#IFRS03_APPA/IFRS03_P0297">acquirer<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0005"/></ph></xref> accounts for <xref base="F4230870" href="IFRS03_APPA.dita#IFRS03_APPA/IFRS03_P0319">intangible assets<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0193"/></ph></xref> acquired in a <xref base="F4230842" href="IFRS03_APPA.dita#IFRS03_APPA/IFRS03_P0304">business combination<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0025"/></ph></xref> in accordance with the provisions of <xref id="IFRS03_X0430" base="F5311840" href="../ias38/IAS38_TOC0001.dita#IAS38_TOC0001">IAS 38 <ph outputclass="standard_ref"><ph outputclass="standard_title">Intangible Assets</ph></ph></xref>. However, as described in <xref id="IFRS03_X0431" base="F5311842" href="../ias38/IAS38_3.dita#IAS38_3">paragraph 3 of IAS 38</xref>, the accounting for some acquired <xref base="F4230870" href="IFRS03_APPA.dita#IFRS03_APPA/IFRS03_P0319">intangible assets<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0193"/></ph></xref> after initial recognition is prescribed by other IFRSs.</p></body></paragraph>